<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="94" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/46.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Calhoun</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In reply to May 16. Sheng Kung Pao is specially entrusted by Prince
                            Regent with work of improving river conditions in famine district. He
                            will gladly accept offer of Red Cross to furnish American engineer. He
                            hopes the latter will come as soon as possible. He will organize corps
                            of necessary assistants. Situation requires prompt attention.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>